I keep getting errors when trying to run base yagsl code with Spark Maxes connected to NEOs. Here are the errors I am encountering from the roboRio:

  • ********** Robot program starting **********

  • NT: Listening on NT3 port 1735, NT4 port 5810

  • NT: Got a NT4 connection from 172.22.11.1 port 29639

  • NT: CONNECTED NT4 client ‘shuffleboard@1’ (from 172.22.11.1:29639)

  • Instantiating NavX on roboRIO MXP Port.

  • NavX: Library for FRC

  • NavX: Connected.

  • NavX: Board Type 50 (navX2-MXP (Gen 2))

  • NavX: firmware version 4.0.447

  • NavX: startup initialization and startup calibration complete.

  • NavX: onboard startup calibration complete.

  • NavX: Yaw angle auto-reset to 0.0 due to startup calibration.

  • [CAN SPARK] IDs: 2, Invalid parameter value, parameter id (113) Velocity Conversion Factor, invalid value is nan

  • Unhandled exception: java.lang.IllegalStateException: Invalid parameter value, parameter id

  • Error at com.revrobotics.spark.SparkBase.configure(SparkBase.java:300): Unhandled exception: java.lang.IllegalStateException: Invalid parameter value, parameter id

  • at com.revrobotics.spark.SparkBase.configure(SparkBase.java:300)

  • The robot program quit unexpectedly. This is usually due to a code error.

    See Reading Stacktraces — FIRST Robotics Competition documentation for more information.

  • at com.revrobotics.spark.SparkMax.configure(SparkMax.java:90)

  • at swervelib.motors.SparkMaxSwerve.lambda$burnFlash$1(SparkMaxSwerve.java:373)

  • at swervelib.motors.SparkMaxSwerve.configureSparkMax(SparkMaxSwerve.java:99)

  • The startCompetition() method (or methods called by it) should have handled the exception above.

  • at swervelib.motors.SparkMaxSwerve.burnFlash(SparkMaxSwerve.java:371)

  • at swervelib.SwerveModule.(SwerveModule.java:163)

  • at swervelib.parser.SwerveDriveConfiguration.createModules(SwerveDriveConfiguration.java:62)

  • at swervelib.parser.SwerveDriveConfiguration.(SwerveDriveConfiguration.java:45)

  • at swervelib.parser.SwerveParser.createSwerveDrive(SwerveParser.java:172)

  • at frc.robot.subsystems.swervedrive.SwerveSubsystem.(SwerveSubsystem.java:90)

  • at frc.robot.RobotContainer.(RobotContainer.java:34)

  • at frc.robot.Robot.robotInit(Robot.java:46)

  • at edu.wpi.first.wpilibj.TimedRobot.startCompetition(TimedRobot.java:107)

  • at edu.wpi.first.wpilibj.RobotBase.runRobot(RobotBase.java:419)

  • at edu.wpi.first.wpilibj.RobotBase.startRobot(RobotBase.java:510)

  • at frc.robot.Main.main(Main.java:27)

  • Warning at edu.wpi.first.wpilibj.RobotBase.runRobot(RobotBase.java:433): The robot program quit unexpectedly. This is usually due to a code error.

  • The above stacktrace can help determine where the error occurred.

Hey OP,

Check this thread:
https://www.chiefdelphi.com/t/ids-8-received-parameter-invalid-error-parameter-id-113/481477/6

We’re currently working through getting swerve working with YAGSL as well. For this specific error, I see that you have the example json configuration from the YAGSL github. You’ll have to update the physicalproperties.json conversionFactor to the new “conversionFactors” which has additional data. See below for an example:

  "conversionFactors": {
    "angle": {"gearRatio": 21.4285714286, "factor": 16.8},
    "drive": {"gearRatio": 6.75, "diameter": 4, "factor": 0.0472867872}
  },

apologies for the slow response.

I noticed in your actual Module JSON files you are using
“type”: “sparkmax”
try swapping those to
“type”: “sparkmax_neo”

and see if that fixes anything. It looks like your main issue is with the SparkMax motor controllers, specifically in relation to the swervelib. Those JSON files should really be the only place that you are manually referencing them, and the rest is handled by the YAGSL library.
